nodes.bodyText: I just saw, I forgot to remove this line. If there is nothing else that needs to be adjusted, I will remove it in feature/permissions
I would rather suggest a regex for this. Because if we ever fill the other colons of the GRN no one will remember this. Let's make it future proof. I can help you with that if you need help
And we should now definitely write some minimal tests for this.
We might need this in the future. So I would advise to to move this to the GRN lib and call it getRouteFromGRN(grn: GRN) what do you think? And does the id not already contain the type?

Remove shared entities mock from EntityShareStore

Add link for title in shared entites overview
Add ifPermitted for owners of a shared entity
Improve GRN handling and add tests
Extract logic to generate show url based on a GRN

nodes.bodyText:
Routes.getPluginRoute
is what you want to use here. Otherwise it thorws an error if enterprise is not installed

Either you mock Routes.getPluginRoute for teams or you do not test it at all.
Since you can't ensure that enterprise plugin is checked out. Especially for open source users.
